<li id="cite_note-McDermott2017-15"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-McDermott2017_15-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFMcDermott2017" class="citation book">McDermott, Joe M. (2017). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=gYvUDAAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PT5"><i>The Fortress at the End of Time</i></a>. <a href="/wiki/Tor_Books" title="Tor Books">Tom Doherty Associates</a>. p.&#160;1. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-7653-9280-0" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-7653-9280-0"><bdi>978-0-7653-9280-0</bdi></a>. <q>We are born as memories and meat. The meat was spontaneously created in the ansible's quantum re-creation mechanism, built up from water vapor, hydrogen, carbon dioxide, and various other gases out of storage. The memory is what we carry across from one side of the ansible to the other, into the new flesh.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Fortress+at+the+End+of+Time&amp;rft.pages=1&amp;rft.pub=Tom+Doherty+Associates&amp;rft.date=2017&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-7653-9280-0&amp;rft.aulast=McDermott&amp;rft.aufirst=Joe+M.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DgYvUDAAAQBAJ%26pg%3DPT5&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAnsible" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/></span>
</li>
</ol></div>
